This paper is primarily focused on the detection and classification of Android malware, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning algorithms to improve the accuracy of malware detection, which is a common topic in the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of static analysis to analyze the behavior and permissions of malicious applications is also a key aspect of the paper, which is relevant to the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of similarity scoring to classify malware into similar groups, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG).
